{"source_key":"sha256-364390994d45a450aa62c8b6d3ca2577","record_index":627,"record_hash":"sha256:304c87c8f6bd72022822fd02ed5f4d6f9a6cd2c6b5707589475d5ce0ba6ad590","timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:19:05.181Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Findings:\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:399](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:399): `setup_repo()` no longer forces `main`, but [line 764](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:764) asserts `refs/heads/main`. `gix::init` can honor `init.defaultBranch`, so this is machine/config brittle. Force `init.defaultBranch=main` via isolated `gix::ThreadSafeRepository::init_opts`, or restore explicit init.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:670](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:670): the concurrent test is good intent, but weak against the regression it names. The barrier only aligns thread start; without the lock, scheduling can still naturally serialize the two captures and pass with `[0, 1]`. Better split this: a small `capture_lock` test proving mutual exclusion with an atomic “inside critical section” counter, plus a plain sequential dedupe test here.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:405](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:405): `commit_file()` is heavy for test setup: tree editor + `but_testsupport::open_repo` + `safe_checkout`. That couples agentlog tests to checkout behavior. Small simplification: make a focused “repo with one committed file” helper that explicitly sets HEAD/main and materializes the worktree, or reuse an existing test fixture helper if one fits.\\n\\nMostly okay: the new capture tests protect real persisted behavior, not just implementation. The weakest mirror-y bits are [lines 737-745](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:737): `not failed`, summary/detail status equality, and `file_count == files.len()` add little. I’d replace them with `snapshot_status == \\\"complete\\\"` for the happy path and keep the path assertions.\\n\\nValidation: `cargo nextest` isn’t installed; targeted `cargo test -p but-agentlog concurrent_capture_serializes_dedupe` passed 5x, and `cargo test -p but-agentlog capture_turn_stores` passed.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:19:05.181Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}